Title : Wolff & Zwicker Iron Works
Text : {{short description|ironworks and shipbuilding company}}

[[File:USS Fox - 19-N-14-26-4.jpg|thumb|[[USS Fox (TB-13)]] at the Wolff & Zwicker Iron Works, Portland, Oregon, probably shortly before she was launched on 4 July 1898.]]
'''Wolff & Zwicker Iron Works''' was an American [[ironworks]] and [[shipbuilding]] company located in [[Portland, Oregon]] from about 1893 until it went into [[receivership]] in 1900.  Its plant was destroyed by fire on June 22, 1902.<ref name=NYT>{{cite news |url= http://cdnc.ucr.edu/cgi-bin/cdnc?a=d&d=LAH19020622.2.6 |title= Bad Blaze in Portland |newspaper= [[Los Angeles Herald]] |date= June 22, 1902 |accessdate= April 30, 2014}}</ref> It built three of the early [[torpedo boat]]s, the [[USS Davis (TB-12)|USS ''Davis'']], the [[USS Fox (TB-13)|USS ''Fox'']], and the [[USS Goldsborough (TB-20)|USS ''Goldsborough'']] for the [[United States Navy]].

